<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:44PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Roanoke and west central Bedford Counties and the northeastern City
of Roanoke through 715 PM EDT...
At 644 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stewartsville, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Vinton...
Stewartsville...
Goodview...
and Chamblissburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
